Class PatientLocation

  • java.lang.Object
    • PatientLocation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<PatientLocation>

    public class PatientLocation
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<PatientLocation>
    PatientLocation is a class that contains the id, name, and room number of a patient in a hospital. Patients are uniquely identified by their last name, first name and id number combination. Note that in this version, there are only 99 possible unique id numbers, but it can be increased easily by altering the code.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(PatientLocation other)
        Determines an order between this patient and the other patient. Order is determined by lastname, then firstname and then id.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<PatientLocation>
        Parameters:
        other - The other patient to compare.
        Returns:
        A value less than zero if this patient is ordered before the other patient, Zero if equals(other) is true, and a value greater than zero if this patient is ordered after the other patient.
